<i>Kaei / Shadow of a Flower (1961)</i>

3
00:01:32,975 --> 00:01:35,293
One Saturday in late April

4
00:01:36,066 --> 00:01:36,899
Here?

5
00:01:37,374 --> 00:01:38,882
You'd be happy.

6
00:01:41,433 --> 00:01:42,653
Thank you very much

7
00:01:43,428 --> 00:01:44,321
Hello!

8
00:01:45,316 --> 00:01:46,076
Welcome.

9
00:01:46,507 --> 00:01:47,427
You look happy.

10
00:01:47,451 --> 00:01:48,710
I will also be on holiday from tomorrow

11
00:01:48,756 --> 00:01:52,118
Toku-san, is the madam still in the hospital?

12
00:01:52,329 --> 00:01:53,309
You look great.
Oh, you're wearing an overcoat

13
00:01:53,584 --> 00:01:54,637
Kan-san

14
00:01:54,682 --> 00:01:56,289
Are you planning to go hunting in Hokkaido?

15
00:01:56,670 --> 00:01:58,237
Hey come on!

16
00:01:58,676 --> 00:01:59,878
I'm going to do Fishing

17
00:02:01,896 --> 00:02:02,784
What can I get you?

18
00:02:02,929 --> 00:02:04,026
The usual one is fine.

19
00:02:04,051 --> 00:02:04,846
Whiskey with water

20
00:02:04,871 --> 00:02:05,539
What about you guys?

21
00:02:05,586 --> 00:02:06,353
 I'll have a beer

22
00:02:06,903 --> 00:02:07,690
I'll have a beer too.

23
00:02:07,850 --> 00:02:09,031
Where are you taking it?

24
00:02:09,056 --> 00:02:10,333
The east coast of Izu.

25
00:02:10,358 --> 00:02:10,933
By car?

26
00:02:11,170 --> 00:02:13,567
Right, I'll get there then

27
00:02:14,119 --> 00:02:17,045
I'll set out by boat while it's still.

28
00:02:17,070 --> 00:02:19,092
Take me there too

29
00:02:19,306 --> 00:02:20,355
Me too, me too

30
00:02:20,399 --> 00:02:22,927
Look, there's a lot of wind outside.
You shouldn't go

31
00:02:22,958 --> 00:02:24,925
What will happen if the wind blows out?

32
00:02:25,530 --> 00:02:26,616
We might be on newspaper

33
00:02:26,695 --> 00:02:28,335
Two Jokyu of you were dead in the water

34
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:30,247
No way!

35
00:02:30,272 --> 00:02:31,439
We are not Jokyu

36
00:02:31,869 --> 00:02:32,477
Why?

37
00:02:32,502 --> 00:02:34,079
That's so old-fashioned

38
00:02:34,450 --> 00:02:36,019
What's the point?

39
00:02:36,043 --> 00:02:36,975
They don't say "hostess" anymore

40
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:37,926
So what do they say?

41
00:02:37,951 --> 00:02:39,001
It's a hostess

42
00:02:39,632 --> 00:02:40,256
That's right, a hostess

43
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:42,706
Hostess? Looks like a self-propelled drug

44
00:02:44,419 --> 00:02:48,460
There are no more Jokyu people anymore in Ginza

45
00:02:48,495 --> 00:02:51,495
But there's no one like Yo-chan here in Ginza

46
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:53,488
She's the last Jokyu

47
00:03:29,842 --> 00:03:30,968
Hey come on.

48
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:35,291
If I don't catch any fish, I'll head back right away.

49
00:03:36,951 --> 00:03:37,571
Welcome.

50
00:03:37,692 --> 00:03:39,172
Don't make weird noises.

51
00:03:39,376 --> 00:03:40,249
Madam

52
00:03:40,367 --> 00:03:42,887
Don't call me like that.
Welcome.

53
00:03:43,191 --> 00:03:43,971
Don't worry

54
00:03:44,351 --> 00:03:45,091
Thanks

55
00:03:45,735 --> 00:03:47,161
The sign outside is broken.

56
00:03:49,717 --> 00:03:51,591
Ginza has great hostesses.

57
00:03:54,123 --> 00:03:56,427
Please be considerate about Toku-san when I'm not around.

58
00:03:56,683 --> 00:03:58,507
I'm sorry

59
00:04:01,022 --> 00:04:03,484
You sneaked out of the hospital

60
00:04:05,842 --> 00:04:06,775
Who is this?

61
00:04:07,636 --> 00:04:09,496
Aya-chan introduced me to this customer

62
00:04:10,269 --> 00:04:11,525
Because of him

63
00:04:11,550 --> 00:04:13,356
Be careful not to steal our customers

64
00:04:15,712 --> 00:04:18,110
You and Yo-chan have to be really strong

65
00:04:19,095 --> 00:04:20,244
By the way, where's Yo-chan?

66
00:04:20,378 --> 00:04:21,185
where's Yo-chan?

67
00:04:21,401 --> 00:04:22,517
She went to drug store

68
00:04:24,322 --> 00:04:25,109
Drug store?

69
00:04:30,446 --> 00:04:31,346
Oh, Jun-chan

70
00:04:32,210 --> 00:04:33,528
Another escape from the hospital?

71
00:04:36,246 --> 00:04:38,598
What? What happened?

72
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:40,635
You look so beautiful tonight?

73
00:04:41,661 --> 00:04:42,782
Right?

74
00:04:43,794 --> 00:04:45,611
If only you could get motivated

75
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:48,880
I'm no good, I don't have the talent to be madam

76
00:04:50,495 --> 00:04:52,591
Toku-san, give me a highball.

77
00:04:52,844 --> 00:04:54,805
It's okay, I'll pay in cash

78
00:04:57,981 --> 00:04:59,545
You're a little drunk

79
00:04:59,999 --> 00:05:01,842
I can tell right away because you lick your lower lip

80
00:05:02,255 --> 00:05:02,875
Scotch

81
00:05:05,594 --> 00:05:07,253
What's wrong with your health

82
00:05:08,931 --> 00:05:10,158
I was going to buy some sleeping pills.

83
00:05:11,552 --> 00:05:11,979
Eh?

84
00:05:15,547 --> 00:05:17,307
I can't sleep these days

85
00:05:18,872 --> 00:05:19,766
I see

86
00:05:21,026 --> 00:05:24,026
When I think about this store, I can't sleep either

87
00:05:24,370 --> 00:05:25,836
What if I close here?

88
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:28,234
I wonder if I should really sell here.

89
00:05:29,367 --> 00:05:32,182
Oh, you owe this much to Takashima-sensei again

90
00:05:32,693 --> 00:05:33,880
It can't be helped

91
00:05:35,214 --> 00:05:36,905
I feel sorry for him, I can't refuse

92
00:05:36,930 --> 00:05:38,569
You have absolutely no talent to be Madam.

93
00:05:43,638 --> 00:05:46,035
Hello, this is Tombo

94
00:05:47,476 --> 00:05:48,601
Please wait a moment

95
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,058
From hospital

96
00:05:50,979 --> 00:05:51,945
Don't be loud

97
00:05:52,570 --> 00:05:54,162
Please tell him I'll be back soon

98
00:05:54,780 --> 00:05:57,006
Hello, She's back soon

99
00:05:57,669 --> 00:05:59,682
Well then, I'm counting on you

100
00:06:01,222 --> 00:06:04,222
Toku-san, please do your best to collect money

101
00:06:06,136 --> 00:06:07,663
I'll send her.

102
00:06:08,549 --> 00:06:10,565
Okay,Don't force yourself

103
00:06:10,590 --> 00:06:12,326
Take care of here

104
00:06:12,350 --> 00:06:13,196
Be careful

105
00:06:25,074 --> 00:06:26,311
Ah, She is here!

106
00:06:26,812 --> 00:06:27,832
It's been ages

107
00:06:28,157 --> 00:06:29,340
Welcome

108
00:06:29,539 --> 00:06:31,293
Let's have a toast for the last Jokyu, okay?

109
00:06:32,333 --> 00:06:32,969
What?

110
00:06:33,001 --> 00:06:35,340
Oh well, let's have a toast for Yo-chan.

111
00:06:36,329 --> 00:06:37,589
I'll have it.

112
00:06:38,396 --> 00:06:39,889
Let's have a toast

113
00:06:50,534 --> 00:06:51,771
I'll go too

114
00:06:54,757 --> 00:06:56,564
This is for car fee

115
00:06:56,616 --> 00:06:57,622
Please share this

116
00:06:57,827 --> 00:06:58,581
But...

117
00:06:58,703 --> 00:06:59,755
Don't worry.

118
00:06:59,780 --> 00:07:00,676
Because it's a hassle

119
00:07:01,195 --> 00:07:01,862
Take it

120
00:07:01,994 --> 00:07:02,592
Sorry

121
00:07:03,180 --> 00:07:04,225
Well, I'll give it back tomorrow

122
00:07:04,250 --> 00:07:05,796
Oh no, tomorrow is Sunday

123
00:07:05,821 --> 00:07:07,131
Oh, I see

124
00:07:07,318 --> 00:07:08,118
Driver

125
00:07:08,507 --> 00:07:10,795
Please have a safe drive.

126
00:07:11,037 --> 00:07:11,984
Trust me

127
00:07:12,009 --> 00:07:13,101
Hey come on

128
00:07:13,745 --> 00:07:15,876
Good night, good night

129
00:07:22,538 --> 00:07:24,551
Good night

130
00:10:22,370 --> 00:10:28,186
The letter was a suicide note addressed to his mother-in-law who lives in Mishima

131
00:10:30,610 --> 00:10:35,259
From this moment on, the timetable for this woman's life was set

132
00:10:48,323 --> 00:10:52,894
Once dawn broke, she tidied up the things she had left behind,

133
00:10:54,038 --> 00:10:57,038
sent this with the key by mail by evening,

134
00:10:57,890 --> 00:11:00,394
and then all she had to do was take the medicine

135
00:11:05,820 --> 00:11:14,566
However, speaking of a timetable for life, Yoko may have thought about it a long time ago

136
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:26,428
About two years ago in an Autumn

137
00:11:51,272 --> 00:11:55,835
My child said that Tsuyuko said
she would die with my wife

138
00:11:58,049 --> 00:11:59,290
Once you hear it, I understand.

139
00:12:00,137 --> 00:12:03,490
My wife and even my kids say the same thing

140
00:12:05,713 --> 00:12:09,204
But thinking about dying and actually dying are different things

141
00:12:12,580 --> 00:12:14,125
But Tsuyuko is 11

142
00:12:15,476 --> 00:12:21,845
She found out about  that her
mother was suffering so much that she wanted to die

143
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:27,800
She doesn't talk when she sees my face

144
00:12:28,290 --> 00:12:30,441
She was the one who chased after me so much,

145
00:12:45,339 --> 00:12:46,276
Close the window

146
00:12:59,837 --> 00:13:02,262
Are you suffering?

147
00:13:04,803 --> 00:13:06,555
No, I'm prepared

148
00:13:07,972 --> 00:13:10,345
Even if the young lady dies?

149
00:13:10,370 --> 00:13:11,906
she won't die

150
00:13:11,930 --> 00:13:15,503
She thought she would become disabled in her legs due to polio.

151
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,686
She won't die

152
00:13:17,710 --> 00:13:19,337
because she know it was misdiagnosis

153
00:13:19,580 --> 00:13:20,746
As long as she doesn’t die,

154
00:13:20,777 --> 00:13:21,576
that's fine for you?

155
00:13:25,226 --> 00:13:28,226
Anyway, I don't think I can stay here for a while.

156
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:31,373
I received my manuscript fee.

157
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:33,329
Here are 100,000 yen,

158
00:13:35,471 --> 00:13:36,938
but I don't need money

159
00:13:38,270 --> 00:13:41,131
Let's break up instead

160
00:13:41,858 --> 00:13:42,809
It's better,right?

161
00:13:43,730 --> 00:13:46,730
No, I didn't mean to show it like that

162
00:13:48,266 --> 00:13:50,362
Even if you talk about love and romance

163
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:52,675
The ending of all relationships is the same

164
00:13:58,653 --> 00:14:00,643
I really was going to get married with you.

165
00:14:01,870 --> 00:14:07,319
Even if I quit college, I could get by on my current income. That was my intention

166
00:14:09,670 --> 00:14:10,338
But

167
00:14:10,363 --> 00:14:10,700
 it's okay,

168
00:14:10,725 --> 00:14:12,013
you don't have to make excuses

169
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:16,520
But the word marriage

170
00:14:17,331 --> 00:14:19,529
Today is the first time I've heard it from your mouth,

171
00:14:20,912 --> 00:14:22,888
we were together for 3 years though.

172
00:14:25,706 --> 00:14:28,482
I wish I'd heard those words at least sooner

173
00:14:29,420 --> 00:14:30,756
Even if it's a lie

174
00:14:30,890 --> 00:14:31,336
No

175
00:14:32,057 --> 00:14:37,067
and even when we break up, you
don't even say a word about breaking up

176
00:14:38,590 --> 00:14:42,997
No, I'm not lying, I still have no intention of breaking up

177
00:14:43,728 --> 00:14:45,175
I want to be with you.

178
00:14:46,198 --> 00:14:47,298
That's enough

179
00:14:49,518 --> 00:14:50,999
I don't need a lot of money anymore

180
00:14:51,460 --> 00:14:53,812
I've had enough of this
enclosed life

181
00:14:59,430 --> 00:15:02,430
But we've been together up until now,

182
00:15:02,510 --> 00:15:03,775
so don't make fun of me

183
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:06,266
Don't even try to make fun of other people's feelings

184
00:15:07,006 --> 00:15:10,006
Just go home. Whose house is this?

185
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:13,677
If that's your house

186
00:15:14,196 --> 00:15:15,178
then please go home.

187
00:15:16,801 --> 00:15:17,310
Yoko,

188
00:15:19,416 --> 00:15:20,329
Leave

189
00:15:24,088 --> 00:15:25,154
I don't want to break up with you.

190
00:15:27,645 --> 00:15:29,337
Let's think about each other again

191
00:15:30,606 --> 00:15:31,539
Yoko.

192
00:16:16,618 --> 00:16:17,258
Yoko.

193
00:16:18,384 --> 00:16:19,481
that's all

194
00:16:19,740 --> 00:16:21,350
Your precious things

195
00:16:24,351 --> 00:16:26,659
But how do you plan to get on with your life from now on?

196
00:16:29,759 --> 00:16:32,759
Mishima's mother won't be worried about you

197
00:16:34,495 --> 00:16:35,615
I'll be fine.

198
00:16:37,610 --> 00:16:40,610
Ever since I was forced to quit girls' school at 15,

199
00:16:40,940 --> 00:16:42,776
I've been living off the emptiness of Ginza

200
00:16:46,220 --> 00:16:48,535
I'll consult with Takashima

201
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:49,539
Takashima-san ?

202
00:16:51,131 --> 00:16:53,160
He is a genius when it comes to Antiques

203
00:16:53,877 --> 00:16:55,024
His character is bad.

204
00:17:34,562 --> 00:17:36,168
Please take good care of your daughter

205
00:17:38,917 --> 00:17:39,377
Yap

206
00:17:40,163 --> 00:17:41,690
I won't see you off

207
00:19:05,730 --> 00:19:07,685
Jun-chan is at the store yet?

208
00:19:07,732 --> 00:19:08,392
Not yet.

209
00:19:08,784 --> 00:19:10,011
I'll stop by later

210
00:19:12,308 --> 00:19:14,725
Takashima-sensei is at the grave behind

211
00:19:37,442 --> 00:19:40,238
Oh, Yoko

212
00:19:40,270 --> 00:19:42,128
It's been a while.

213
00:19:44,780 --> 00:19:46,406
Oh, I heard you broke up with Matsuzaki

214
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,222
He brought it up?

215
00:19:54,722 --> 00:19:55,396
No.

216
00:19:56,092 --> 00:19:57,006
I told him

217
00:19:57,611 --> 00:20:00,991
I've been told by you to break up with him

218
00:20:01,570 --> 00:20:04,570
That's true, but that's ridiculously sudden

219
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:05,863
Come on up

220
00:20:14,385 --> 00:20:15,539
Yoko there?

221
00:20:22,689 --> 00:20:23,713
Jun-chan

222
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:25,436
I was going to stop by later though

223
00:20:25,460 --> 00:20:26,599
But I'm going out

224
00:20:27,330 --> 00:20:28,772
About Matsuzaki-san?

225
00:20:29,205 --> 00:20:30,538
Well, yap

226
00:20:30,780 --> 00:20:32,802
That turned out to be a good thing.

227
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:34,496
Even though he's a university professor,

228
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:35,823
he's a person with no money

229
00:20:35,966 --> 00:20:37,756
You've been following him up until now

230
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,186
So how much did you get?

231
00:20:41,710 --> 00:20:43,256
I can't get it

232
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:44,536
That person is poor

233
00:20:45,086 --> 00:20:46,948
Plus the kid is sick

234
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:48,793
You are stupid.

235
00:20:49,620 --> 00:20:52,043
You've wasted three years of your prime

236
00:20:53,190 --> 00:20:56,190
You should send him 30,000 yen every month.

237
00:20:56,359 --> 00:20:58,255
I'm disgusted with you

238
00:20:58,283 --> 00:20:59,536
You're too kind

239
00:20:59,835 --> 00:21:01,178
It's good

240
00:21:01,210 --> 00:21:03,166
Because she says she doesn't need it

241
00:21:03,191 --> 00:21:04,904
But....

242
00:21:07,551 --> 00:21:09,311
what are you going to do from now on?

243
00:21:11,101 --> 00:21:12,781
I'm here to consult about it

244
00:21:15,439 --> 00:21:19,384
The woman who worked in Ginza have no choice but to go back to Ginza.

245
00:21:20,299 --> 00:21:22,025
I'll have to find some place

246
00:21:24,009 --> 00:21:25,995
Why not just have her come to Tombo?

247
00:21:26,047 --> 00:21:26,874
Tombo?

248
00:21:27,774 --> 00:21:30,385
Did you open another bar besides Clara?

249
00:21:30,410 --> 00:21:30,991
Yap

250
00:21:32,716 --> 00:21:35,259
that's why I wanted the money

251
00:21:35,599 --> 00:21:38,565
That's how much preparation you need to do to work in Ginza

252
00:21:38,590 --> 00:21:40,226
Professor Takashima,There is calling

253
00:21:41,075 --> 00:21:43,473
You don't want to owe it out yourself,

254
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:54,655
Even if he says something arrogant

255
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:57,276
Unlike before, his wallet is empty

256
00:21:57,300 --> 00:21:59,656
Even the antiques in this room is gone every time he come s here

257
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:02,680
But they are belong to him

258
00:22:03,090 --> 00:22:05,156
But he has a brother

259
00:22:05,180 --> 00:22:06,462
and is currently in court

260
00:22:06,940 --> 00:22:08,836
Say big things like 30 million yen,

261
00:22:08,860 --> 00:22:11,233
but you won't know until you actually hold the money

262
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:14,150
He hasn't paid his rent for a while.

263
00:22:14,586 --> 00:22:17,586
But I wonder if that has anything to do with the value of him?

264
00:22:18,585 --> 00:22:21,198
You are always on Takashima side

265
00:22:23,503 --> 00:22:25,457
Your ex boyfriend Matsuzaki said that too

266
00:22:25,971 --> 00:22:27,938
He told Takashima didn't work

267
00:22:28,544 --> 00:22:31,077
Work is not the only measure of a person's worth.

268
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:34,742
Isn't it more admirable to be respected
without doing anything?

269
00:22:35,140 --> 00:22:36,644
That's a strange logic

270
00:22:40,656 --> 00:22:43,656
Oh, I've known Matsuzaki for three years

271
00:22:44,448 --> 00:22:46,175
I've just started to work with Takashima

272
00:22:46,527 --> 00:22:48,251
You've been friends with the teacher for almost 20 years

273
00:22:48,350 --> 00:22:51,351
Isn't  the only one who respects Takashima is you

274
00:22:52,630 --> 00:22:53,802
But, you know,

275
00:22:54,497 --> 00:23:00,102
All the customers at the bar try to hit on you when they get drunk.

