00:37:34,850 --> 00:37:36,450
but be careful of Hata-san.

554
00:37:59,240 --> 00:38:01,333
Come on, Yo-chan,

555
00:38:06,497 --> 00:38:08,146
I'm sorry

556
00:38:12,540 --> 00:38:15,416
It's okay now, I'm used to coming home drunk

557
00:38:15,440 --> 00:38:16,770
Maybe we should have some tea?

558
00:38:17,156 --> 00:38:20,012
I did, but then the rehearsal started again

559
00:38:45,318 --> 00:38:45,926
Hata-san

560
00:38:48,207 --> 00:38:49,825
You're probably thinking
I'm being too persistent

561
00:38:50,121 --> 00:38:52,208
I just couldn't stay still like that

562
00:38:55,486 --> 00:38:57,661
I won't get a response until tomorrow night

563
00:38:58,860 --> 00:39:01,348
I don't like this place,
take me somewhere else,

564
00:39:26,630 --> 00:39:28,106
You were sleeping comfortably

565
00:39:33,500 --> 00:39:34,794
Go to take another bath

566
00:39:38,690 --> 00:39:40,040
What's wrong?

567
00:39:41,125 --> 00:39:41,801
What time is it now?

568
00:39:43,742 --> 00:39:44,555
It's a little after 11 o'clock

569
00:39:45,620 --> 00:39:47,278
There don't seem to be many customers tonight,

570
00:39:47,303 --> 00:39:48,909
so I think you can sleep in

571
00:39:48,934 --> 00:39:50,208
I'm going home,

572
00:39:50,687 --> 00:39:51,853
what's the matter?

573
00:39:51,878 --> 00:39:53,149
Let me do that

574
00:39:56,337 --> 00:39:59,442
I'll give you my marriage proposal tomorrow.

575
00:40:24,294 --> 00:40:26,637
Who is it? Hata-san?

576
00:40:26,989 --> 00:40:28,270
Oyo, it's me

577
00:40:28,803 --> 00:40:33,653
What's wrong, teacher? Teacher,
you're not even wearing a scarf.

578
00:40:34,026 --> 00:40:35,265
It's gotten cold

579
00:40:35,290 --> 00:40:36,614
Oh, let me have one

580
00:40:37,630 --> 00:40:39,426
I got robbed at mahjong yesterday

581
00:40:39,450 --> 00:40:41,028
I barely made it this far

582
00:40:41,500 --> 00:40:42,596
Did you lose that much?

583
00:40:42,621 --> 00:40:43,403
5,000 yen

584
00:40:43,521 --> 00:40:45,130
I even left a debt

585
00:40:46,215 --> 00:40:48,240
Are you hungry?

586
00:40:48,355 --> 00:40:49,800
your stomach is fine,

587
00:40:49,825 --> 00:40:51,270
but please give me back some delicious pickles

588
00:40:54,966 --> 00:40:56,153
Didn't you go to work today?

589
00:40:56,482 --> 00:40:59,482
No, I went to Mishima to relax

590
00:41:00,099 --> 00:41:03,309
Didn't your mom say something
terrible again?

591
00:41:04,360 --> 00:41:05,756
Talking about marriage

592
00:41:05,780 --> 00:41:08,137
You were pretty serious yesterday,

593
00:41:08,464 --> 00:41:10,926
She's not my confidant.

594
00:41:13,009 --> 00:41:16,442
I regret not telling you it was yesterday

595
00:41:17,180 --> 00:41:19,762
But in the end,
don't you want to get married?

596
00:41:22,032 --> 00:41:24,262
Does that seem like how I see it?

597
00:41:25,341 --> 00:41:27,833
Oh, I'm sorry

598
00:41:41,657 --> 00:41:44,926
Oyo, don't deceive yourself

599
00:41:46,560 --> 00:41:51,356
Well, I don't want to marry you, but

600
00:41:52,470 --> 00:41:55,470
Hata-san doesn't seem like as bad a person as people say,

601
00:41:57,340 --> 00:41:59,825
but I just can't make up my mind

602
00:41:59,850 --> 00:42:01,312
You are confused

603
00:42:02,317 --> 00:42:03,567
To be honest

604
00:42:04,730 --> 00:42:06,645
Well then, I have something to say

605
00:42:07,250 --> 00:42:08,192
What?

606
00:42:08,968 --> 00:42:12,684
I think marriage is bad for you.

607
00:42:13,410 --> 00:42:15,286
Not just Hata

608
00:42:16,324 --> 00:42:19,345
In other words, how should I put it? In short,

609
00:42:19,385 --> 00:42:23,747
I don't think you'll be happy if you get married.

610
00:42:25,150 --> 00:42:26,778
It seems that's the case

611
00:42:27,215 --> 00:42:29,426
Marriage is a kind of deal.

612
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:34,520
Whether it's money or love, you only get along if you have each other's long asses

613
00:42:35,121 --> 00:42:38,856
You have no experience doing that

614
00:42:40,567 --> 00:42:42,935
Many men have fallen in love with you

615
00:42:44,384 --> 00:42:48,450
but no matter what, you always give it back twice or three times as much

616
00:42:50,210 --> 00:42:51,458
That's why it doesn't matter

617
00:42:54,945 --> 00:42:55,720
Yes, thank you

618
00:42:57,044 --> 00:42:59,435
This is very delicious.

619
00:43:00,263 --> 00:43:01,208
oh, you're right

620
00:43:03,014 --> 00:43:04,090
I'm stupid

621
00:43:04,427 --> 00:43:06,778
no, you're too good for a woman

622
00:43:08,030 --> 00:43:10,575
Matsuzaki once told me that too

623
00:43:11,230 --> 00:43:13,256
In the end, I'm a villain

624
00:43:13,280 --> 00:43:17,114
But there is such a thing

625
00:43:18,810 --> 00:43:21,810
Well, if he loves you, then I don't care what happens

626
00:43:22,640 --> 00:43:25,286
I just wish you'd stopped getting married

627
00:43:25,311 --> 00:43:26,481
It's sad though

628
00:43:28,720 --> 00:43:32,528
Well, there's no rule that every woman has
to have a husband.

629
00:43:33,410 --> 00:43:35,200
It's more comfortable being alone

630
00:43:36,771 --> 00:43:38,091
It could be.

631
00:43:39,387 --> 00:43:41,348
Yeah, I was also muttering after breaking up with Matsuzaki.

632
00:43:41,458 --> 00:43:43,482
You shouldn't act tough anymore

633
00:43:44,270 --> 00:43:45,809
It will snap completely

634
00:43:46,448 --> 00:43:51,708
It's safer if you stay low and creeps along the ground

635
00:43:52,630 --> 00:43:54,476
So you're saying to keep a low profile

636
00:43:54,500 --> 00:43:55,696
Oh, you're smart

637
00:44:01,715 --> 00:44:03,634
But it's strange

638
00:44:03,840 --> 00:44:05,169
When I was talking to the teacher,

639
00:44:06,010 --> 00:44:07,536
I felt a lot of things building up inside me

640
00:44:08,802 --> 00:44:13,020
It always feels like the lump is gone all at once

641
00:44:13,530 --> 00:44:14,669
Oh, I see.

642
00:44:15,539 --> 00:44:16,873
I've already eaten.

643
00:44:18,388 --> 00:44:19,372
Eat some ochazuke

644
00:44:19,511 --> 00:44:20,575
I'm going home now.

645
00:44:20,600 --> 00:44:22,317
Oh, you just got here

646
00:44:22,889 --> 00:44:24,614
That's all I have left of my life.

647
00:44:25,271 --> 00:44:27,552
Why don't you stay? The wind is blowing.

648
00:44:28,060 --> 00:44:28,857
Thank you for the meal

649
00:44:29,080 --> 00:44:29,926
I'll come again

650
00:44:30,445 --> 00:44:34,583
Oh, right? You don't have any money,do you? Yes,

651
00:44:39,919 --> 00:44:41,465
I have 3,000 yen

652
00:44:41,490 --> 00:44:42,756
Take it with you

653
00:44:42,780 --> 00:44:44,028
So, shall I borrow it?

654
00:44:44,376 --> 00:44:46,981
Junko gets mad when I get into debt

655
00:44:47,420 --> 00:44:48,395
Ah, teacher

656
00:45:04,138 --> 00:45:05,271
Be careful.

657
00:45:15,520 --> 00:45:17,403
Is it okay here? It's cold,

658
00:45:17,428 --> 00:45:18,465
so please pick it up quickly

659
00:45:19,552 --> 00:45:20,973
Please give me some extra film too.

660
00:45:21,346 --> 00:45:23,372
Don't show this to Hata

661
00:45:24,170 --> 00:45:25,086
Another one

662
00:45:25,110 --> 00:45:25,965
Squat there

663
00:45:28,224 --> 00:45:29,232
I can't see you much these days,

664
00:45:29,280 --> 00:45:30,645
but maybe you're not letting me in?

665
00:45:30,899 --> 00:45:33,505
Do you not want your boyfriend to spend money?

666
00:45:33,530 --> 00:45:35,190
Don't be cheeky.

667
00:45:35,410 --> 00:45:36,473
Boy?

668
00:45:37,200 --> 00:45:38,239
Stand up.

669
00:45:39,113 --> 00:45:41,622
Your dad pays the bill for this bar.

670
00:45:42,177 --> 00:45:43,676
You are still child

671
00:45:43,739 --> 00:45:45,208
Oh my god.

672
00:45:46,450 --> 00:45:49,450
When you say that, what's so funny about men coming to bars?

673
00:45:49,863 --> 00:45:52,119
Probably no one will come for fun

674
00:45:52,870 --> 00:45:55,416
I don't think there are any girls who enjoy working there

675
00:45:55,440 --> 00:45:56,895
It's a strange place,

676
00:45:58,097 --> 00:45:59,531
Definitely

677
00:46:00,330 --> 00:46:01,614
In other words....

678
00:46:01,639 --> 00:46:02,864
Give it to me

679
00:46:02,889 --> 00:46:03,825
Be careful.

680
00:46:05,137 --> 00:46:10,786
In other words, the anxiety.....someone with no talent like me can't do a job like directing a TV show

681
00:46:10,830 --> 00:46:13,516
And I am constantly being chased by time

682
00:46:13,540 --> 00:46:15,551
It becomes like a kind of neurosis

683
00:46:15,880 --> 00:46:18,056
Confidence is gone and anxiety is building

684
00:46:18,080 --> 00:46:20,646
That's when I need to come to the bar

685
00:46:20,670 --> 00:46:21,966
By your Dad's money

686
00:46:21,990 --> 00:46:23,567
You say it again.

687
00:46:23,592 --> 00:46:25,645
Hey you, let's take a photo

688
00:46:25,670 --> 00:46:30,145
Oh yeah, your dad was a TV executive

689
00:46:30,270 --> 00:46:33,028
Stop it about saying my dad.

690
00:46:33,678 --> 00:46:36,090
Hey, Professor Takashima

691
00:46:37,489 --> 00:46:40,095
please put him on an educational TV show or something?

692
00:46:40,260 --> 00:46:41,776
If that's the case,

693
00:46:41,800 --> 00:46:44,419
I don't have to tell my dad, I'll talk to the programming director myself.

694
00:46:44,444 --> 00:46:45,130
Come in.

695
00:46:45,723 --> 00:46:46,911
Excuse me.

696
00:46:46,936 --> 00:46:48,559
but can you go ahead for a bit?

697
00:46:51,192 --> 00:46:51,927
Yo-chan.

698
00:46:51,959 --> 00:46:53,169
Can't you see Hata-san?

699
00:46:53,194 --> 00:46:53,794
No

700
00:46:53,974 --> 00:46:54,755
oh, that's right.

701
00:46:55,020 --> 00:46:57,976
I just came downstairs with a customer so I stopped by

702
00:46:58,000 --> 00:46:58,756
About his bill?

703
00:46:59,684 --> 00:47:03,020
sorry, I haven't forgotten, but how much was it?

704
00:47:03,208 --> 00:47:04,005
Sorry.

705
00:47:04,872 --> 00:47:07,778
Well, it's not right to ask you to do that

706
00:47:07,990 --> 00:47:10,458
Anyway, his bill has already accumulated

707
00:47:11,489 --> 00:47:12,886
Come inside and wait for a bit

708
00:47:12,910 --> 00:47:14,032
Oh, I see.

709
00:47:14,445 --> 00:47:16,299
Toku-san

710
00:47:22,497 --> 00:47:24,364
I'm short on 2000 yen. Can you lend me
some?

711
00:47:24,935 --> 00:47:26,739
Yo-chan, it's time to stop messing around

712
00:47:27,072 --> 00:47:30,677
There's no need to pay Mr. Hata's bill.

713
00:47:31,078 --> 00:47:34,762
Because I got him to buy Christmas tickets

714
00:47:36,809 --> 00:47:40,165
It looks you are giving me 10,000 yen in change for a 1,000 yen bill

715
00:47:43,396 --> 00:47:44,817
Sorry.

716
00:47:55,656 --> 00:47:57,270
Good evening.

717
00:47:57,638 --> 00:47:58,771
Aya-chan is off?

718
00:47:59,442 --> 00:48:00,716
Hey Yo-chan. I need to talk with you.

719
00:48:09,262 --> 00:48:11,090
What's wrong? You've got a scary look on your face.

720
00:48:11,717 --> 00:48:14,717
I'm so angry.
Can't you be the only one who's okay?

721
00:48:15,951 --> 00:48:17,605
I'm so frustrated,

722
00:48:17,727 --> 00:48:18,754
so what's wrong?

723
00:48:19,153 --> 00:48:20,975
Look,
it's Clara on 7th Street

724
00:48:21,000 --> 00:48:22,536
There was a place that was trying to replace that.

725
00:48:22,560 --> 00:48:24,097
In the basement of a building in Higashi Ginza

726
00:48:25,110 --> 00:48:26,777
That spot got stolen away from me.

727
00:48:29,801 --> 00:48:32,535
Guess who it was? It was Ayako.

728
00:48:34,199 --> 00:48:37,941
She used me to get that spot.

729
00:48:42,430 --> 00:48:44,105
And moreover

730
00:48:44,266 --> 00:48:47,683
It was Hata who gave the push
and brought the matter together

731
00:48:49,309 --> 00:48:50,129
Hata?

732
00:48:51,847 --> 00:48:59,060
Didn't you know? I thought Ayako had a lot of days off recently, and it turns out they went to Osaka together,

733
00:48:59,085 --> 00:49:00,900
to prepare the money for that.

734
00:49:02,110 --> 00:49:03,439
Ayako is Ayako,

735
00:49:03,710 --> 00:49:05,267
and Hata is Hata, right?

736
00:49:05,628 --> 00:49:08,142
He pretended to marry you.

737
00:49:09,090 --> 00:49:10,501
You were trying to pay his bills,right?

738
00:49:11,300 --> 00:49:13,157
I'm totally shocked
and don't like it

739
00:49:13,890 --> 00:49:16,890
Yoko, Hata is here

740
00:49:21,142 --> 00:49:22,275
Kumi-chan

741
00:49:23,447 --> 00:49:25,103
 what's wrong with you?

742
00:49:25,900 --> 00:49:27,275
You know what?

743
00:49:28,416 --> 00:49:29,924
What's wrong?

744
00:49:44,299 --> 00:49:45,385
It's been ages.

745
00:49:45,642 --> 00:49:46,895
How are you?

746
00:49:46,920 --> 00:49:49,306
Yes, thanks to you,

747
00:49:49,330 --> 00:49:50,345
that's good

748
00:49:51,180 --> 00:49:52,572
It's so cold

749
00:49:53,040 --> 00:49:55,275
You are prone to catching colds

750
00:50:01,509 --> 00:50:04,007
Oh, by the way, Matsuko wants to meet you

751
00:50:04,740 --> 00:50:06,346
Look, that big doll

752
00:50:06,370 --> 00:50:07,776
you gave her for Christmas

753
00:50:07,800 --> 00:50:09,931
She still sleep with it by her pillow.

754
00:50:11,830 --> 00:50:16,314
I've also been in a bit of trouble lately with the Kanto Electric Railway's land acquisition

755
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:19,056
After all, it's a government job

756
00:50:19,080 --> 00:50:20,636
I'm very busy

757
00:50:20,661 --> 00:50:26,838
Oh yeah, I thought you were busy buying up bars in Higashi Ginza again

758
00:50:27,410 --> 00:50:28,076
What?

759
00:50:31,699 --> 00:50:34,010
How did you like Osaka?

760
00:50:34,611 --> 00:50:36,220
You felt like a newlywed couple?

761
00:50:38,634 --> 00:50:40,362
Yes, I guess you're serious this time

762
00:50:41,110 --> 00:50:42,384
The other person is a young person

763
00:50:43,300 --> 00:50:44,314
What are you talking about?

764
00:50:44,423 --> 00:50:46,134
Because you're a great person too

765
00:50:46,431 --> 00:50:49,430
It's about time to pretend to slam your head on the tatami mat.

766
00:50:50,160 --> 00:50:51,846
What's wrong with this girl?

767
00:50:53,734 --> 00:50:56,202
You should stop trying to get a hold of the hostess' money.

768
00:50:58,546 --> 00:50:59,827
Stop it

769
00:51:02,804 --> 00:51:04,109
Stay strong.

770
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:11,047
Are you alright?

771
00:51:25,130 --> 00:51:26,327
You're a crybaby

772
00:51:27,844 --> 00:51:29,422
I'm not going to cry

773
00:51:31,390 --> 00:51:33,554
I've been in Hostess of Ginza for over ten years

774
00:51:35,040 --> 00:51:36,890
I have had many experiences like this.

775
00:51:37,860 --> 00:51:39,851
It's mostly because Yo-chan was spoiled too much

776
00:51:40,650 --> 00:51:42,359
I warned her

777
00:51:43,625 --> 00:51:45,601
but I an really that stupid

778
00:51:46,308 --> 00:51:47,820
Remember that

779
00:51:48,350 --> 00:51:51,350
Yes, yes, I want to be stupid too,

780
00:51:51,670 --> 00:51:53,749
but it seems like my turn never comes

781
00:51:57,382 --> 00:51:58,898
You're cheeky.

782
00:52:39,983 --> 00:52:41,346
I don't care if anyone knows.

783
00:52:42,639 --> 00:52:44,350
Even Takashima-sensei?

784
00:52:45,366 --> 00:52:46,405
It can't be helped.

785
00:53:00,639 --> 00:53:05,827
Come on, you idiot, it's already noon and you have a book reading at 1 o'clock,right?

786
00:53:07,731 --> 00:53:09,390
Oh wait a minute?

787
00:53:11,190 --> 00:53:13,466
I'm so happy
they finally changed it

788
00:53:13,490 --> 00:53:16,490
This is the first time someone has asked me to change my hair style

789
00:53:16,515 --> 00:53:18,476
Yeah, it's absolutely wonderful

790
00:53:21,734 --> 00:53:23,560
I think you should put out a bit more here

791
00:53:23,585 --> 00:53:26,226
You're too noisy

792
00:53:26,380 --> 00:53:27,456
Even in actresses' hair

793
00:53:27,480 --> 00:53:28,766
I often claim

794
00:53:28,790 --> 00:53:30,741
Now I'm ready,

795
00:53:41,999 --> 00:53:43,230
You are sleeping again.

796
00:53:44,030 --> 00:53:47,030
You see, the smell of you still lingers

797
00:53:47,730 --> 00:53:48,656
You idiot.

798
00:53:50,554 --> 00:53:51,789
Are you there?

799
00:53:52,781 --> 00:53:53,828
It's Takashima Sensei

800
00:54:06,757 --> 00:54:08,038
Excuse me.

801
00:54:08,211 --> 00:54:09,594
Don't worry.

802
00:54:10,050 --> 00:54:12,106
I was thinking of going to visit Junko

803
00:54:12,130 --> 00:54:13,179
I came to invite you

804
00:54:15,383 --> 00:54:16,206
Excuse me.

805
00:54:16,231 --> 00:54:17,390
You're welcome

806
00:54:21,590 --> 00:54:23,023
You changed your hair

807
00:54:23,670 --> 00:54:25,413
I wonder if that's Shimizu's hobby

808
00:54:26,455 --> 00:54:27,773
What about dinner, Sensei?

809
00:54:27,798 --> 00:54:28,902
It's lunchtime.

810
00:54:29,417 --> 00:54:32,390
Please try the eel bowl.
I've only made enough for two people

811
00:54:32,710 --> 00:54:35,710
This is the real "thank you for the meal" thing.

812
00:54:35,922 --> 00:54:37,015
I'll call then

813
00:54:45,020 --> 00:54:46,085
Please have some tea.

814
00:54:48,523 --> 00:54:49,344
Is this yours? Oh,

815
00:54:49,593 --> 00:54:50,406
Yo-chan's

816
00:54:52,569 --> 00:54:55,406
but do you have about 5,000 yen with you? Oh,

817
00:54:55,479 --> 00:54:56,929
if you have that much

818
00:54:59,484 --> 00:55:03,281
there's a shop called Nihon
Hobby Store at the Yaesu exit that caters to tourists

819
00:55:03,866 --> 00:55:08,210
I can pay you back right away once I've decided a deal about the Muromachi pottery

820
00:55:08,410 --> 00:55:09,351
Anytime is fine.

821
00:55:10,366 --> 00:55:11,734
Don't tell Oyo about it

822
00:55:20,370 --> 00:55:22,386
Surely you were single

823
00:55:22,411 --> 00:55:22,914
Yes.

824
00:55:23,529 --> 00:55:27,445
Oyo still has the heart of a child

825
00:55:28,240 --> 00:55:30,116
That's how I like her

826
00:55:30,990 --> 00:55:34,734
There's something so sweet
about her little expressions and gestures

827
00:55:35,218 --> 00:55:38,218
Are you going to marry her?

828
00:55:39,453 --> 00:55:41,594
No, no, I haven't decided yet

829
00:55:43,787 --> 00:55:46,787
She seems to have given up on marriage.

830
00:55:47,447 --> 00:55:49,748
But it seems like she wants a little

831
00:55:50,150 --> 00:55:53,150
Please think about that for a moment.

832
00:55:54,733 --> 00:55:55,991
Ah, it's cold.

833
00:56:07,054 --> 00:56:08,234
Are you surprised?

834
00:56:09,142 --> 00:56:11,335
I've been dyeing it secretly up until now

835
00:56:13,120 --> 00:56:15,499
I'm scared to look in the mirror every day

836
00:56:16,710 --> 00:56:18,171
It's not that bad

837
00:56:19,229 --> 00:56:21,187
If you just stay still, you'll get better soon

838
00:56:21,476 --> 00:56:22,297
No...

839
00:56:23,430 --> 00:56:25,491
I knew this would happen someday

840
00:56:26,731 --> 00:56:29,241
If it wasn't lung disease, I'd be cancer

841
00:56:30,080 --> 00:56:33,080
But you're not worried about money

842
00:56:33,453 --> 00:56:34,179
That's good

843
00:56:35,023 --> 00:56:36,250
That's not true

844
00:56:36,970 --> 00:56:39,970
It's okay though, because I sold Clara on 7th Street

845
00:56:40,270 --> 00:56:43,820
As for Tombo, you and Toku are the only ones I can rely on,

846
00:56:44,400 --> 00:56:45,826
so please do your best

847
00:56:46,092 --> 00:56:47,374
You're getting greedy again

848
00:56:48,054 --> 00:56:50,695
money, money, this is your punishment for making so much money

849
00:56:55,116 --> 00:56:57,452
What would happen if I became like this?

850
00:56:59,033 --> 00:57:02,033
So, you should save money or get married

851
00:57:02,380 --> 00:57:04,702
I'm saying you have to choose one or the other

852
00:57:06,710 --> 00:57:08,546
It's about time for you too

853
00:57:10,240 --> 00:57:13,240
If Shimizu-san could marry you

854
00:57:13,981 --> 00:57:15,027
As for Hata

855
00:57:15,727 --> 00:57:18,160
If you had felt that way, you would have gotten together

856
00:57:18,439 --> 00:57:21,104
Hey, hey, you may know a lot about money,

857
00:57:21,160 --> 00:57:22,738
but what about getting marriage?

858
00:57:22,809 --> 00:57:24,129
Stop complaining

859
00:57:25,200 --> 00:57:27,886
That's right, I have something to talk to Yo-chan about

860
00:57:28,500 --> 00:57:29,941
Can you please leave your seat for a moment?

861
00:57:30,240 --> 00:57:31,691
What's going on?

862
00:57:31,716 --> 00:57:33,543
I can't tell this to a man

863
00:57:33,802 --> 00:57:35,738
Oh, I am waiting in the hallway

864
00:57:44,094 --> 00:57:45,160
What,Jun-chan?

865
00:57:46,481 --> 00:57:50,449
Takashima-sensei is broken in the end

866
00:57:52,020 --> 00:57:54,716
I heard it from someone who came to visit me just now

867
00:57:54,740 --> 00:57:58,629
You know, the story about the 30 million yen mansion?

868
00:57:59,480 --> 00:58:02,004
Apparently the bank took it away from him
to pay off his debt,

869
00:58:03,888 --> 00:58:08,886
and nowadays, He seems to be selling fakes.

870
00:58:11,060 --> 00:58:15,129
The person lamented that the antiques world's
records have also fallen to the ground

871
00:58:17,430 --> 00:58:20,430
The world has become a difficult place for people like him to live in

872
00:58:21,570 --> 00:58:23,980
It's not the world's fault

873
00:58:27,970 --> 00:58:32,855
In these harsh times, there's no way he can make a living with such a cheap business

874
00:58:34,768 --> 00:58:36,894
Should I ask the teacher to come to my house?

875
00:58:38,690 --> 00:58:40,722
Don't say stupid things

876
00:58:41,850 --> 00:58:46,363
Even his old friends don't pay him
any attention anymore

877
00:58:47,160 --> 00:58:48,800
Even those people

878
00:58:48,980 --> 00:58:50,776
When teachers used to have money

879
00:58:50,800 --> 00:58:52,699
Everyone was praising the teacher

880
00:58:53,668 --> 00:58:55,574
They were saying he's a genius

881
00:58:56,035 --> 00:58:57,137
That's right.

882
00:58:57,868 --> 00:59:02,636
I wonder why people with such hobbies don't want to give money to the teacher

883
00:59:04,860 --> 00:59:07,566
I don't know much about art or anything,

884
00:59:08,310 --> 00:59:10,355
but the teacher needs money

885
00:59:12,180 --> 00:59:14,527
If I had it, I would give it all to him.

886
00:59:39,428 --> 00:59:41,066
Thank you for the meal!

887
00:59:48,492 --> 00:59:49,738
Good morning.

888
01:00:14,100 --> 01:00:15,644
Good morning.

889
01:00:28,091 --> 01:00:29,105
Yo-chan!

890
01:00:29,285 --> 01:00:30,504
Welcome!

891
01:00:31,520 --> 01:00:32,449
Welcome!

892
01:00:32,580 --> 01:00:35,488
I've brought a rare person with me today

893
01:00:35,677 --> 01:00:36,433
So who is it?

894
01:00:36,723 --> 01:00:38,692
He's liked you for a long time

895
01:00:40,110 --> 01:00:41,418
I wonder what he's doing.

896
01:00:41,660 --> 01:00:43,293
Welcome. Welcome

897
01:00:44,488 --> 01:00:45,340
It's been ages.

898
01:00:49,800 --> 01:00:51,269
Maybe you forgot about me for a while?

899
01:00:51,801 --> 01:00:53,652
that's understandable

900
01:00:54,350 --> 01:00:55,886
It's been 15,6 years.

901
01:00:57,860 --> 01:01:00,106
Wow, Non-chan

902
01:01:02,043 --> 01:01:03,176
I'm sorry

903
01:01:04,480 --> 01:01:05,448
but it was good

904
01:01:05,660 --> 01:01:07,046
I'm glad you remembered me.

905
01:01:08,931 --> 01:01:10,243
Welcome

906
01:01:13,566 --> 01:01:14,915
You look so nice.

907
01:01:15,371 --> 01:01:16,519
I look like grandmother, right?

908
01:01:16,652 --> 01:01:19,324
You are much more attractive than before.

909
01:01:19,603 --> 01:01:22,885
I explained that to you.

910
01:01:22,910 --> 01:01:25,550
He didn't want to ruin the old image,

911
01:01:25,879 --> 01:01:26,965
Hey come on.

912
01:01:27,262 --> 01:01:27,981
Treat me.

913
01:01:28,343 --> 01:01:31,343
Make me drink that most expensive Napoleon whiskey

914
01:01:31,824 --> 01:01:32,707
Welcome

915
01:01:32,754 --> 01:01:33,645
It's fine

916
01:01:33,840 --> 01:01:34,424
Welcome,

917
01:01:34,449 --> 01:01:36,786
this guy was in the same class as me

918
01:01:36,810 --> 01:01:38,636
Unlike us department store managers,

919
01:01:38,660 --> 01:01:39,644
He's bourgeois

920
01:01:40,174 --> 01:01:41,589
Ah, I'm sure it's something like in Kofu

921
01:01:41,614 --> 01:01:42,582
Yes, that's right

922
01:01:42,870 --> 01:01:46,269
He succeeded his father as president of a wine company.

923
01:01:46,451 --> 01:01:48,316
Hey, hey, stop it already.

924
01:01:48,809 --> 01:01:52,324
Anyway, he's having trouble figuring out what to do with the money

925
01:01:53,470 --> 01:01:54,356
Today too

926
01:01:54,380 --> 01:01:58,371
I happened to meet him at the Momoyama
art exhibition in our department store

927
01:01:59,020 --> 01:01:59,826
Well, that's fine

928
01:01:59,850 --> 01:02:01,144
Everyone, please drink as much as you like

929
01:02:01,177 --> 01:02:01,992
Can I have some?

930
01:02:02,584 --> 01:02:04,661
Please, please.
You can drink whatever you like.

931
01:02:04,725 --> 01:02:05,801
Thank you

932
01:02:06,053 --> 01:02:07,082
I'll have brandy cup

933
01:02:07,145 --> 01:02:08,418
Same here.

934
01:02:08,543 --> 01:02:09,230
I'll have juice

935
01:02:09,255 --> 01:02:10,098
I'll have gin.

936
01:02:13,332 --> 01:02:14,051
Thanks.

937
01:02:14,391 --> 01:02:18,151
Back then, all I saw was Non-chan in his school uniform

938
01:02:18,480 --> 01:02:21,480
You should have kept an eye on him then.

939
01:02:21,598 --> 01:02:22,535
Really.

940
01:02:22,560 --> 01:02:24,824
I'm sure I would have become the president's wife

941
01:02:27,215 --> 01:02:29,910
Sorry, I got carried away with the story

942
01:02:30,240 --> 01:02:31,379
What would you like to eat?

943
01:02:31,770 --> 01:02:32,910
This is Napoleon whiskey.

944
01:02:34,129 --> 01:02:35,106
Thanks.

945
01:02:38,449 --> 01:02:40,980
Let's all have a toast.

946
01:02:41,082 --> 01:02:41,723
I'll have.

947
01:02:41,895 --> 01:02:43,527
Cheers!

948
01:02:46,789 --> 01:02:48,105
This, this

949
01:02:51,811 --> 01:02:55,449
You suddenly disappeared back then.

950
01:02:56,300 --> 01:02:58,261
I was dragged into the war,

951
01:02:59,140 --> 01:03:01,008
so if only it hadn't happened....

952
01:03:01,199 --> 01:03:02,277
Stop it....

953
01:03:02,332 --> 01:03:02,910
What?

954
01:03:04,161 --> 01:03:07,847
This guy wanted to marry Yo-chan

955
01:03:08,393 --> 01:03:11,393
Sasagara, You confessed that to us earlier.

956
01:03:12,710 --> 01:03:13,855
I was not lying

957
01:03:14,490 --> 01:03:17,490
But back then, I was still a student living off my parents

958
01:03:18,730 --> 01:03:20,621
You were too popular back then

959
01:03:21,513 --> 01:03:22,447
No way

960
01:03:23,556 --> 01:03:25,822
Yo-chan's customers were amazing back then

961
01:03:26,486 --> 01:03:30,364
Mr. Kikuchi, Biography, Rintaro Takemoto and Shoichi Yokokawa

962
01:03:31,000 --> 01:03:34,000
Also, all the musicians and painters like Soutaro were fans of Yo-chan

963
01:03:34,183 --> 01:03:36,700
and they were wrecking that bar

964
01:03:37,410 --> 01:03:41,045
And look, did you know the art critic Kenzo Takashima?

965
01:03:42,043 --> 01:03:44,183
You knew him?

966
01:03:44,570 --> 01:03:46,306
Yeah

967
01:03:46,330 --> 01:03:47,756
He often scolded me

968
01:03:47,780 --> 01:03:49,843
I don't get lectured often

969
01:03:49,868 --> 01:03:51,288
Was it?

970
01:03:51,700 --> 01:03:52,856
Well, why don't you meet him next time?

971
01:03:52,880 --> 01:03:54,515
I'm sure he'll miss you

972
01:03:54,540 --> 01:03:56,906
Is he still coming here? Of course I want to see him

973
01:03:58,140 --> 01:04:01,140
I'm starting to get interested in antiques

974
01:04:01,660 --> 01:04:03,736
There's something I'd really like him to see

975
01:04:03,760 --> 01:04:05,326
Maybe he'll come by tonight

976
01:04:05,350 --> 01:04:07,220
Tonight? That's a shame

977
01:04:07,560 --> 01:04:09,136
I can't relax much tonight

978
01:04:10,307 --> 01:04:11,066
Oh no, that's no good

979
01:04:11,090 --> 01:04:12,085
I have to go soon

980
01:04:13,876 --> 01:04:15,477
I have to catch a 7 o'clock flight to Kansai

981
01:04:15,502 --> 01:04:17,448
No rush

982
01:04:17,473 --> 01:04:19,109
I don't want to postpone it next time

983
01:04:19,440 --> 01:04:20,866
I'll come back when I've had enough

984
01:04:20,890 --> 01:04:21,933
I'm sure I'll come

985
01:04:22,087 --> 01:04:24,304
Hey Sahara, take your time.

986
01:04:24,813 --> 01:04:25,799
Bill please

987
01:04:26,150 --> 01:04:29,010
If you give us it, I'll lose contact

988
01:04:29,266 --> 01:04:30,702
I will definitely come

989
01:04:30,842 --> 01:04:32,069
I don't trust you

990
01:04:32,848 --> 01:04:34,001
Keep going.

991
01:04:35,458 --> 01:04:36,398
Oh my god.

992
01:04:39,852 --> 01:04:41,948
Oh, that's right. Then I'll leave this here until then

993
01:04:45,240 --> 01:04:46,428
It's a rare watch

994
01:04:46,922 --> 01:04:48,002
My late father's

995
01:04:48,230 --> 01:04:50,456
This was the watch that he gave to his first girl friend

996
01:04:50,480 --> 01:04:52,058
Why do you have that?

997
01:04:54,290 --> 01:04:56,356
I always stay there whenever I'm in Tokyo

998
01:04:56,380 --> 01:04:57,226
Thank you.

999
01:04:57,250 --> 01:04:59,156
Are you dating with her?

1000
01:04:59,180 --> 01:05:00,546
Come on

1001
01:05:00,570 --> 01:05:02,036
She run an inn in Yugawara

1002
01:05:02,060 --> 01:05:03,608
I stayed there yesterday too,

1003
01:05:03,890 --> 01:05:05,360
but I asked her to give it to me

1004
01:05:06,006 --> 01:05:08,362
It seems to be a survivor where my father went to France a long time ago

1005
01:05:09,500 --> 01:05:10,826
That's nice

1006
01:05:11,060 --> 01:05:13,398
If he doesn't come, I'll take it

1007
01:05:19,323 --> 01:05:21,087
That would be a great way to celebrate

1008
01:05:22,764 --> 01:05:24,855
Okay, then I'll lend it to you

1009
01:05:24,880 --> 01:05:26,496
If you like it, use it

1010
01:05:26,520 --> 01:05:28,956
But this is a memento of your father

1011
01:05:28,998 --> 01:05:29,491
Don't worry.

1012
01:05:29,596 --> 01:05:31,205
Just take it

1013
01:05:32,099 --> 01:05:34,098
Wow, I'm so happy.

1014
01:05:34,212 --> 01:05:35,985
Has the customer from Seibi arrived?

1015
01:05:36,585 --> 01:05:38,786
That's right, I have something I'm taking care of

1016
01:05:41,351 --> 01:05:44,138
How about the three of us go to Yugawara together?

1017
01:05:44,258 --> 01:05:44,845
That's great

1018
01:05:44,950 --> 01:05:46,076
shall we go?

1019
01:05:46,100 --> 01:05:50,128
If the teacher goes, I should thank the person who brought this watch.

1020
01:05:50,479 --> 01:05:51,259
That's right.

1021
01:05:56,609 --> 01:06:00,507
Wakanourazu, isn't this unusual for Takihara?

1022
01:06:01,182 --> 01:06:04,182
It's quite good, it's from Edo period, isn't it?

1023
01:06:06,490 --> 01:06:07,043
Is this yours?

1024
01:06:07,110 --> 01:06:10,428
No, I was asked by the publisher

1025
01:06:10,680 --> 01:06:11,506
Is it for sale?

1026
01:06:11,530 --> 01:06:14,176
Yes, there is silver in the gold

1027
01:06:14,200 --> 01:06:16,176
Well, 7 or 80000 yen would be a good deal

1028
01:06:16,390 --> 01:06:18,310
7 or 80000 yen...

1029
01:06:18,610 --> 01:06:20,176
If it was at least 50,000 yen, I'd be ok with it

1030
01:06:20,200 --> 01:06:23,200
Like a child, when I see it, I want it right away

1031
01:06:23,660 --> 01:06:25,043
Yeah, that's good

1032
01:06:25,600 --> 01:06:26,736
Because I was told to leave it to me

1033
01:06:26,761 --> 01:06:27,485
Is that so?

1034
01:06:30,800 --> 01:06:32,067
I'm sorry about that

1035
01:06:34,360 --> 01:06:36,529
Let's take this to Yugawara.

1036
01:06:37,908 --> 01:06:39,748
Thank you very much.

1037
01:06:45,295 --> 01:06:48,408
How about going to an old place tonight?

1038
01:06:48,820 --> 01:06:50,636
Most of the Madam there have changed

1039
01:06:50,660 --> 01:06:53,660
But Lupin and Cytheria

1040
01:06:54,050 --> 01:06:55,936
Just the name sounds nostalgic, doesn't it?

1041
01:06:56,012 --> 01:06:58,106
Okay, come on,
Why don't you join us,Oyo?

1042
01:06:59,933 --> 01:07:01,255
I'll call them

1043
01:07:10,106 --> 01:07:13,597
Oyo, isn't it about time to break up with Shimizu?

1044
01:07:14,763 --> 01:07:16,363
That's not going to happen

1045
01:07:17,598 --> 01:07:20,668
You always fall in love with men who don't have money.

1046
01:08:07,254 --> 01:08:08,011
Good morning

1047
01:08:08,655 --> 01:08:11,655
I heard you were drinking wine with a guy from your company.

1048
01:08:11,680 --> 01:08:12,856
but you couldn't give this back?

1049
01:08:13,098 --> 01:08:15,098
He gave it to me.

1050
01:08:17,845 --> 01:08:19,152
Wow, that's generous.

1051
01:08:25,754 --> 01:08:27,082
So...

1052
01:08:27,549 --> 01:08:29,366
Are you leaving already?

1053
01:08:29,430 --> 01:08:31,324
 Yes,the director is calling me at 11 o'clock

1054
01:08:32,120 --> 01:08:34,956
The ratings for my show have been dropping lately

1055
01:08:34,980 --> 01:08:36,276
I might got scolded

1056
01:08:36,690 --> 01:08:37,973
Then see you on Saturday

1057
01:08:38,356 --> 01:08:40,112
Oh, what was it?

1058
01:08:40,379 --> 01:08:41,319
Oh....

1059
01:08:41,680 --> 01:08:44,006
I told you we were going to Kinugawa for an overnight stay

1060
01:08:45,236 --> 01:08:46,616
I forgot it

1061
01:08:47,300 --> 01:08:48,666
I was in trouble

1062
01:08:48,916 --> 01:08:49,527
Why?

1063
01:08:51,957 --> 01:08:55,112
I promised to go to Yugawara on Sunday.

1064
01:08:55,738 --> 01:08:56,875
With whom?

1065
01:08:57,140 --> 01:09:00,621
Nogata-san and Takashima-sensei

1066
01:09:01,270 --> 01:09:02,160
Can't I do it next time?

1067
01:09:02,185 --> 01:09:04,847
No,I told you yesterday.I won't be off work for a while

1068
01:09:05,249 --> 01:09:06,725
Have you forgotten that?

1069
01:09:08,110 --> 01:09:09,746
I was so drunk yesterday.

1070
01:09:09,771 --> 01:09:10,980
I don't remember anything

1071
01:09:17,460 --> 01:09:21,530
Even if you remember his promises , but you forget my promises

1072
01:09:24,040 --> 01:09:25,975
You shouldn't say it like that,

1073
01:09:26,602 --> 01:09:27,382
Refuse their promise

1074
01:09:28,470 --> 01:09:29,971
That's not the case

1075
01:09:30,291 --> 01:09:31,171
They are my customers

1076
01:09:31,208 --> 01:09:32,463
so just say you received a watch.

1077
01:09:33,679 --> 01:09:35,112
I don't even know what you did yesterday

1078
01:09:37,840 --> 01:09:38,795
Are you serious?

1079
01:09:40,366 --> 01:09:41,606
It's rude to say something like that.

1080
01:09:43,630 --> 01:09:45,357
You are a hostess anyway.

1081
01:09:46,488 --> 01:09:48,055
I've done this kind of drama before

1082
01:09:49,696 --> 01:09:50,663
What do you mean?

1083
01:09:52,390 --> 01:09:56,963
I didn't expect to be humiliated.
You switched to the president of the wine company.

1084
01:09:58,153 --> 01:09:59,313
I am bar woman

1085
01:10:00,126 --> 01:10:02,259
Isn't it natural to cherish the rich?

1086
01:10:02,580 --> 01:10:04,347
If you don't like it, just go home

1087
01:10:09,993 --> 01:10:11,167
I'll go home without being told

1088
01:10:42,423 --> 01:10:45,423
That's right, I owe Takashima-sensei 5,000 yen

1089
01:10:47,020 --> 01:10:48,732
I have 5000 yen in my handbag

1090
01:10:50,140 --> 01:10:52,518
This was the car fee  Nogata-san gave me last night,

1091
01:10:57,565 --> 01:10:58,371
I tell you

1092
01:10:59,476 --> 01:11:03,144
but if you open a girl's handbag without saying anything like that, she'll hate you.

